1.1 Portmanteau Test

port <- function(x, lag, fitdf) { # x = , lag = , fitdf = 
  res <- Box.test(x, lag = lag, type = "Ljung-Box", fitdf = fitdf) # 
#  res <- c(lag, res$statistic, res$parameter, res$p.value) # , , , p 
#  names(res) <- c("m", "Q(m)", "df", "p.value") # 
  res <- res$statistic # 

  return(res)
}

T <- 100 # 
p <- 1; ar <- 0.5 # AR ; AR 
fitdf <- 0 # 
lag <- 1 + fitdf # 
# AR(p) 
x <- arima.sim(n = T, # 
               list(order = c(p, 0, 0), ar = ar)) # AR , AR 
port(x, lag, fitdf)
## X-squared 
##  8.671569

1.2 

port.sim <- function(T, p, ar, mu, # T = , p = AR , ar = AR , mu = 
                     include.mean, fixed, lag, fitdf) { # include.mean = , fixed = , lag = , fitdf = 
  # AR(p) 
  x <- arima.sim(n = T, # 
                 list(order = c(p, 0, 0), ar = ar)) # AR , AR 
  x <- mu + x  # 

  # AR(p) 
  est <- arima(x, # 
               order = c(p, 0, 0), # AR 
               include.mean = include.mean, #  
               transform.pars = F, # 
               fixed = fixed, # 
               method = "CSS") #  2  

  res <- sapply(lag, port, x = est$residuals, fitdf = fitdf) # x  fitdf  lag  port 

  return(res)
}

mu <- 2 # 
include.mean <- TRUE # 
fixed <- rep(NA, p + 1) # 
fitdf <- 0 # 
lag <- 1:4 + fitdf # 
port.sim(T, p, ar, mu, include.mean, fixed, lag, fitdf)
##  X-squared  X-squared  X-squared  X-squared 
## 0.00609874 0.20535692 0.66787722 3.15993732

1.3 QQ plot

port.res.qqplot <- function(x, lag, fitdf) { # x = , lag = , fitdf = 
  n.lag <- length(lag) # 

  for(i in 1:n.lag) {
    # QQ plot
    qqplot(x[i,], # 
           qchisq(ppoints(x[i,]), df = lag[i] - fitdf), # 
           xlab = "x", ylab = "chisq") # 

    # 
    abline(a = 0, b = 1, # , 
           col = 2, lty = 2) # , 
  }
}

1.4 

port.res.hist <- function(x, lag, fitdf) { # x = , lag = , fitdf = 
  n.lag <- length(lag) # 

  for(i in 1:n.lag) {
    # 
    y.max <- max(dchisq(x[i,], df = lag[i] - fitdf)) + 0.1 # y 
    hist(x[i,], # 
         freq = FALSE, # 
         main = "", # 
         ylim = c(0, y.max), # y 
         xlab = "x") # x 

    # 
    curve(dchisq(x, df = lag[i] - fitdf), # 
          add = TRUE, # 
          col = 2, lty = 2, lwd = 2) # , , 
  }
}

1.5 

port.res.mv <- function(x, lag, fitdf) { # x = , lag = , fitdf = 
  res <- cbind(lag - fitdf, apply(x, 1, mean), apply(x, 1, var)) # , , 
  res <- cbind(lag, res) # 
  rownames(res) <- NULL
  colnames(res) <- c("m", "df", "mean", "var") # 

  return(res)
}
